ce progressive JavaScript front-end framework that was built to organize and simplify web development. It is one of the famous frameworks used to simplify web development.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <h2>VueJS Features</h2>\r\n <ul class=\"points\">\r\n   <li><p><strong>Templates</strong> - Vue uses an HTML-based template syntax that allows you to declaratively bind the rendered DOM to the underlying Vue instanceâs data. All Vue templates are valid HTML that can be parsed by spec-compliant browsers and HTML parsers<p></li>\r\n   <li><p><strong>Components</strong> - Components are one of the most powerful features of Vue. They help you extend basic HTML elements to encapsulate reusable code. At a high level, components are custom elements that Vueâs compiler attaches behavior to. In some cases, they may also appear as a native HTML element extended with the special is attribute.<br />All Vue components are also Vue instances, and so accept the same options object (except for a few root-specific options) and provide the same lifecycle hooks.<p></li>\r\n   <li><p><strong>Routing</strong> - vue-router is the official router for Vue.js. It deeply integrates with Vue.js core to make building Single Page Applications with Vue.js a breeze. <p></li>\r\n   <li><p><strong>Event Handling</strong> - v-on directive to listen to DOM events and run some JavaScript when theyâre triggered.<p></li>\r\n   <li><p><strong>Lightweight</strong> - VueJS script is very lightweight and the performance is also very fast.<p></li>\r\n </ul>\r\n</div>',1,1,'VueJS Introduction - nexladder','VueJs - Overview - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1521818760,'2018-03-23 15:26:00','2018-03-31 16:54:20'),(65,9,13,'VueJs - Introduction','vuejs-introduction','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>Vue is a very powerful framework but one of its strengths is that it is very lightweight and easy to pick up. As a matter of fact, in the first recipe you will build a simple but functioning program in minutes, with no setup required</p>\r\n<p><h2>Creating a Vue Instance</h2></p>\r\n<p>Every Vue application starts by creating a new Vue instance with the Vue function:</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">var </span><span class=\"pln\">vm </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"com\"> \r\n     // options</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n})</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the code display \"Hello World\" with Vue.js. The objective here is how Vue manipulates your webpage and how data binding works.</p>\r\n<p>In the JavaScript section, write:</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">e1</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\'})</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>In the HTMLquadrant, we create the:</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"tag\">&lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  {{ message }}</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/div&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><code><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">e1</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\'})</span></code> will instantiate a new Vue instance. It accepts an options object as a parameter. This object is central in Vue, and defines and controls data and behavior. It contains all the information needed to create Vue instances and components. In our case, we only specified the el option which accepts a selector or an element as an argument. The #app parameter is a selector that will return the element in the page with app as the identifier. For example, in a page like this:</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;&lt;h1&gt;{{ message }}&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	e1</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        message</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">Hello World</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app1\"> {{ message }}\r\n</div>\r\n<script>\r\n	 new Vue({\r\n				el: \'#app1\',\r\n				data: {\r\n						message: \'Hello World\'\r\n				}\r\n	 });\r\n</script>\r\n</div>',2,1,'VueJs Introduction - nexladder','VueJs - Introduction - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522321079,'2018-03-29 10:57:59','2018-03-29 11:50:41'),(66,9,14,'VueJs v-text','vuejs-v-text-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><strong>v-text</strong> works just like <strong>{{}}</strong> interpolation. &lt;div v-text=\"content\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; renders the same output as &lt;div&gt;{{ content }}&lt;/div&gt;.</p>\r\n<p>when you pass HTML markup to <code>v-text</code>. It appears that v-text encodes HTML entities such as < and >.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the #Example 1</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;div v-text=\"content\"&gt&lt;/div&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        content</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"tag\">Hello World</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app\">\r\n     <div v-text=\"content\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<script>\r\n    new Vue ({\r\n                el: \'#app\',\r\n    data: {\r\n                content: \'Hello World\'\r\n          }\r\n             })\r\n</script>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the #Example 2</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app1\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;div&gt{{ content }}&lt;/div&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app1</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        content</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"tag\">Hello World</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app1\">\r\n     <div>{{ content }}</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<script>\r\n    new Vue ({\r\n                el: \'#app1\',\r\n    data: {\r\n                content: \'Hello World\'\r\n          }\r\n             })\r\n</script>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the #Example 3</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app2\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;div v-text=\"content\"&gt&lt;/div&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app2</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        content</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;h3&lt;Hello World&lt;/h3&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>In above example, <code>v-text</code> did not render the <code>h3</code> tag. if you want to render the <code>h3</code> tag, you should use <code>v-html</code> directive instead of <code>v-text</code> directive.</p>\r\n</div>  \r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app2\">\r\n     <div v-text=\"content\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<script>\r\n    new Vue ({\r\n                el: \'#app2\',\r\n    data: {\r\n                content: \'<h3<Hello World</h3>\'\r\n          }\r\n             })\r\n</script>\r\n</div>',3,1,'VueJs v-text directive - nexladder','VueJs v-text - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522515570,'2018-03-31 16:59:30','2018-04-01 08:39:01'),(67,9,14,'VueJs v-html','vuejs-v-html-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>v-html</strong> will render them as plain HTML rather than encoding them.</p>\r\n  <p>Updates the element\'s <code>innerHTML</code>. Note that the contents are inserted as plain HTML - they will not be compiled as Vue templates.</p>  \r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the #Example 1</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n       &lt;div v-html=\"content\"&gt&lt;/div&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n          el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n    data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n            content</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;h2&gt;Hello World&lt;/h2&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n    }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>In previous example, <code>v-text</code> did not render the <code>h3</code> tag, here we\'ll use <code>v-html</code> directive to render the <code>&lt;h3&gt;</code></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app\">\r\n     <div v-html=\"content\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<script>\r\n    new Vue ({\r\n                el: \'#app\',\r\n    data: {\r\n                content: \'<h2>Hello World</h2>\'\r\n          }\r\n             })\r\n</script>\r\n</div>',4,1,'VueJs v-html directive - nexladder','VueJs v-html - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522516024,'2018-03-31 17:07:04','2018-04-01 08:47:38'),(68,9,14,'VueJs v-show','vuejs-v-show-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>v-show</strong> will always be rendered and remain in the DOM. v-show only toggles the display CSS property of the element</p>\r\n  <p><strong><i>Note: </i></strong>v-show doesn\'t support the &lt;template&gt; element, nor does it work with v-else.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;div v-show=\"show\"&gt;Hello World!&lt;/div&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        show</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"tag\">true</span><span class=\"pun\"></span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<img src=\"https://nexladder.com/uploads/vuejs_show_directive_true.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-responsive\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n       &lt;div v-show=\"show\"&gt;Hello World!&lt;/div&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n          el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n          data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n                  show</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"tag\">false</span><span class=\"pun\"></span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n          }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n      })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<img src=\"https://nexladder.com/uploads/vuejs_show_directive_false.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-responsive\" />\r\n</div>',5,1,'VueJs v-show directive - nexladder','VueJs v-show - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522516231,'2018-03-31 17:10:31','2018-04-04 00:28:17'),(69,9,14,'VueJs v-if','vuejs-v-if-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>v-if</strong> directive adds or removes DOM elements based on the given expression.We can use the show property from the data model and show a Hello World in the view.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;div v-if=\"show\"&gt;Hello World!&lt;/div&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        show</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"tag\">false</span><span class=\"pun\"></span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p>Now, the \"Hello World\" will not show because show is set to false. Setting the data.show value to true would add the Hello World to the DOM.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<img src=\"https://nexladder.com/uploads/vuejs_if_directive_false.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-responsive\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app1\"&gt;\r\n       &lt;div v-if=\"show\"&gt;Hello World!&lt;/div&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n          el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app1</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n    data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n            show</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"tag\">true</span><span class=\"pun\"></span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n    }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<img src=\"https://nexladder.com/uploads/vuejs_if_directive_true.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-responsive\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n     <h2>difference between the v-show and v-if</h2>\r\n     <ul class=\"points\">\r\n	  <li>v-if - Only renders the element to the DOM if the expression passes.</li>\r\n	  <li>v-show - Renders all elements to the DOM and then uses the CSS display property to hide elements if the expression fails.</li>\r\n	  <li>v-show - Does not support v-else, v-else-if</li>\r\n	 </ul>\r\n</div>',6,1,'VueJs v-if directive - nexladder','VueJs v-if - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522516411,'2018-03-31 17:13:31','2018-04-04 00:34:32'),(70,9,14,'VueJs v-for','vuejs-v-for-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>v-for</strong> directive allows us to loop through items in an array or object. it requires a special syntax in the form of <code>item in list</code>, where list is the source data array and item is an alias for the array element being iterated on:</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"tag\">&lt;ul&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n  &lt;li v-for=\"item in list\">{{ item }}&lt;/li&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>This will output an unordered list with the values from the array.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;ul id=\"app2\"&gt;\r\n	    &lt;li v-for=\"item in list\">{{ item.name }}&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;/ul&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app2</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n			data</span><span class=\"pln\">:</span><span class=\"pln\">{</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n				  list</span><span class=\"pln\">: [</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						{</span><span class=\"pln\"> name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Apple</span><span class=\"pun\">\' }, </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						{</span><span class=\"pln\"> name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Mango</span><span class=\"pun\">\' }, </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						{</span><span class=\"pln\"> name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Banana</span><span class=\"pun\">\' }, </span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n					]</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			  }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<ul id=\"app\">\r\n	    <li v-for=\"item in list\">{{ item.name }}</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n        	el: \'#app\',\r\n			data:{\r\n				  list: [\r\n						{ name: \'Apple\' }, \r\n						{ name: \'Mango\' }, \r\n						{ name: \'Banana\' }, \r\n					]\r\n			  }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p>Inside <code>v-for</code> blocks we have full access to parent scope properties. <code>v-for</code> also supports an optional second argument for the index of the current item.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;ul id=\"app3\"&gt;\r\n	    &lt;li v-for=\"(item, index) in list\">{{ heading }} : {{ index }} - {{ item.name }}&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;/ul&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app3</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n			data</span><span class=\"pln\">:</span><span class=\"pln\">{</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			          heading</span><span class=\"pln\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">item with index</span><span class=\"pln\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n				  list</span><span class=\"pln\">: [</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						{</span><span class=\"pln\"> name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Apple</span><span class=\"pun\">\' }, </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						{</span><span class=\"pln\"> name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Mango</span><span class=\"pun\">\' }, </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						{</span><span class=\"pln\"> name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Banana</span><span class=\"pun\">\' }, </span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n					]</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			  }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<ul id=\"app1\">\r\n	    <li v-for=\"(item, index) in list\">{{ heading }} : {{ index }} - {{ item.name }}</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n        	el: \'#app1\',\r\n			data:{\r\n			          heading: \'item with index\', \r\n				  list: [\r\n						{ name: \'Apple\' }, \r\n						{ name: \'Mango\' }, \r\n						{ name: \'Banana\' }, \r\n					]\r\n			  }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>v-for with objects</h2>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;ul id=\"app3\"&gt;\r\n	    &lt;li v-for=\"(item, key, index) in list\">{{ item }} : {{ key }} - {{ index }}&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;/ul&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app3</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n			data</span><span class=\"pln\">:</span><span class=\"pln\">{</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n				  list</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						</span><span class=\"pln\"> index1</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Orange</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						</span><span class=\"pln\"> index2</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Apricots</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						</span><span class=\"pln\"> index3</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Strawberry</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n					}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			  }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<ul id=\"app2\">\r\n	    <li v-for=\"(item, key, index) in list\">{{ item }} : {{ key }} - {{ index }}</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n        	el: \'#app2\',\r\n			data:{\r\n				  list: {\r\n						 index1: \'Orange\', \r\n						 index2: \'Apricots\', \r\n						 index3: \'Strawberry\', \r\n					}\r\n			  }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h3><code>v for</code> with <code>v-if</code></h3>\r\n<p>When they exist on the same node, v-for has a higher priority than v-if. That means the v-if will be run on each iteration of the loop separately. This can be useful when you want to render nodes for only some items, like below:</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"tag\">&lt;ul&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n  &lt;li v-for=\"item in list\" v-if=\"item.show\">{{ item }}&lt;/li&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;ul id=\"app3\"&gt;\r\n	    &lt;li v-for=\"item in list\" v-if=\"item.show\">{{ item.name }}&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;/ul&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app3</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n			data</span><span class=\"pln\">:</span><span class=\"pln\">{</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n				  list</span><span class=\"pln\">: [</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						{</span><span class=\"pln\"> name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Apple</span><span class=\"pun\">\',</span><span class=\"pln\"> show</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"str\">true</span><span class=\"pun\">}, </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						{</span><span class=\"pln\"> name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Mango</span><span class=\"pun\">\',</span><span class=\"pln\"> show</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"str\">false</span><span class=\"pun\">}, </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n						{</span><span class=\"pln\"> name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">Banana</span><span class=\"pun\">\',</span><span class=\"pln\"> show</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"str\">true</span><span class=\"pun\">}, </span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n					]</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			  }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<ul id=\"app3\">\r\n	    <li v-for=\"item in list\" v-if=\"item.show\">{{ item.name }}</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n        	el: \'#app3\',\r\n			data:{\r\n				  list: [\r\n						{ name: \'Apple\', show: true}, \r\n						{ name: \'Mango\', show: false}, \r\n						{ name: \'Banana\', show: true}, \r\n					]\r\n			  }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>Below an example to add a username in an array and display in a listing</h2>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;div id=\"app4\"&gt;\r\n	  &lt;p v-if=\"error\" class=\"error\"&gt;{{ error }}&lt;/p&gt;\r\n      &lt;input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Enter your name\" name=\"username\" value=\"\" v-model=\"username\"  /&gt;&lt;button type=\"button\" @click=\"add\">Click me&lt;/button&gt;\r\n      &lt;ul&gt;\r\n        &lt;li v-for=\"item in users\"&gt;{{ item.name }}&lt;/li&gt;\r\n      &lt;/ul&gt;\r\n    &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app4</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n			data</span><span class=\"pln\">:</span><span class=\"pln\">{</span><span class=\"pln\"><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			        error</span><span class=\"pun\">:\'\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			        username</span><span class=\"pun\">:\'\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			        username1</span><span class=\"pun\">:\'\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			        username2</span><span class=\"pun\">:\'\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			        username3</span><span class=\"pun\">:\'\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			        username</span><span class=\"pun\">:\'\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			        users</span><span class=\"pun\">:</span><span class=\"pun\">[</span><span class=\"pun\">{\"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\":\"</span><span class=\"str\">Evan You\"</span><span class=\"pun\">},</span><span class=\"pun\">{\"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\":\"</span><span class=\"str\">Vijay Singh\"</span><span class=\"pun\">},</span><span class=\"pun\">{\"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\":\"</span><span class=\"str\">Saarthak Singh\"</span><span class=\"pun\">}],</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			},</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			methods</span><span class=\"pun\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			  add</span><span class=\"pun\">() {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			          if</span><span class=\"pun\"> (!</span><span class=\"pln\">this.username</span><span class=\"pun\">)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n				         {</span><span class=\"str\">\r\n					   this.error</span><span class=\"pun\"> = \'</span><span class=\"pln\">Please enter your name</span><span class=\"pun\">\';</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n					   return</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n					}</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n				   else</span><span class=\"str\">\r\n					    this.error</span><span class=\"pun\"> = \'\';</span><span class=\"str\">\r\n			         this.users.push</span><span class=\"pun\">({\'</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\':</span><span class=\"str\">this.username</span><span class=\"pun\">});</span><span class=\"str\">\r\n				 this.username</span><span class=\"pun\"> = </span><span class=\"pun\">\'\';</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			  },</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;style scoped&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n       .error</span><span class=\"pun\"> {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n	      color</span><span class=\"pun\">:</span><span class=\"pln\">#c82829</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	}</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/style&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<div id=\"app4\">\r\n	  <p v-if=\"error\" class=\"error\">{{ error }}</p>\r\n      <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Enter your name\" name=\"username\" value=\"\" v-model=\"username\"  /><button type=\"button\" @click=\"add\">Click me</button>\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <li v-for=\"item in users\">{{ item.name }}</li>\r\n      </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n        	el: \'#app4\',\r\n			data:{\r\n			        error:\'\',\r\n			        username:\'\',\r\n			        username1:\'\',\r\n			        username2:\'\',\r\n			        username3:\'\',\r\n			        username:\'\',\r\n			        users:[{\"name\":\"Evan You\"},{\"name\":\"Vijay Singh\"},{\"name\":\"Saarthak Singh\"}],\r\n			},\r\n			methods: {\r\n			  add() {\r\n			          if (!this.username)\r\n				         {\r\n					   this.error = \'Please enter your name\';\r\n					   return;\r\n					}\r\n				   else\r\n					    this.error = \'\';\r\n			         this.users.push({\'name\':this.username});\r\n				 this.username = \'\';\r\n			  },\r\n			}\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n   <style scoped>\r\n       .error {\r\n	      color:#c82829;\r\n	}\r\n   </style>\r\n</div>',7,1,'VueJs v-for directive - nexladder','VueJs v-for - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522516632,'2018-03-31 17:17:12','2018-04-03 02:49:05'),(71,9,14,'VueJs v-on','vuejs-v-on-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>v-on</strong> v-on is the attribute added to the DOM elements to listen to the events.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the example</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;button class=\"btn-primary\" v-on:click=\"clickevent\"&gt;click me&lt;/button&gt;\r\n		 &lt;h3&gt;{{ content }}&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		     content</span><span class=\"pln\"> : </span><span class=\"pln\">\'\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		},</span><span class=\"pun\"><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		 methods</span><span class=\"pun\"> : {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		                 clickevent</span><span class=\"pun\"> : </span><span class=\"kwd\">function</span><span class=\"pun\">() {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			                return this.content</span><span class=\"pun\"> = \"</span><span class=\"pln\">Hello World</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			          }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		             }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	})</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n <div id=\"app1\">\r\n       <button class=\"btn-primary\" v-on:click=\"clickevent\">click me</button>\r\n     <h3>{{ content }}</h3>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n          el: \'#app1\',\r\n    data: {\r\n         content : \'\',\r\n    },\r\n     methods : {\r\n                     clickevent : function() {\r\n                      return this.content = \"Hello World\"\r\n                }\r\n                 }\r\n  })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',8,1,'VueJs v-on directive - nexladder','VueJs v-on - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522516744,'2018-03-31 17:19:04','2018-03-31 17:48:32'),(72,9,14,'VueJs v-bind','vuejs-v-bind-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>v-bind</strong> is used to dynamically bind one or more attributes, or a component prop to an expression.</p>\r\n  <p>When used to bind the class or style attribute, it supports additional value types such as Array or Objects.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the example of bind the attribute <code>href</code> and img <code>src</code></p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;a v-bind:href=\"href\"&gt;\r\n		   &lt;img alt=\"\" v-bind:src=\"imgsrc\" /&gt;\r\n	     &lt;/a&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        href</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">https://nexladder.com</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        imgsrc</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">https://nexladder.com/images/nexlogo.png</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>  \r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n <div id=\"app1\">\r\n       <a v-bind:href=\"href\">\r\n       <img alt=\"\" v-bind:src=\"imgsrc\" />\r\n       </a>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n          el: \'#app1\',\r\n    data: {\r\n            href: \'https://nexladder.com\', \r\n            imgsrc: \'https://nexladder.com/images/nexlogo.png\'\r\n    }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',9,1,'VueJs v-bind directive - nexladder','VueJs v-bind - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522516882,'2018-03-31 17:21:22','2018-03-31 17:42:38'),(73,9,14,'VueJs v-model','vuejs-v-model-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>v-model</strong> varies based on value of form inputs element or output of components.</p>\r\n  <p>v-model directive that makes two-way binding between form input and app state a breeze.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the example</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;input placeholder=\"enter your name\"type=\"text\" name=\"name\" value=\"\" v-model=\"name\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;div&gt; {{ name }} &lt;/div&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'\'</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>  \r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app1\">\r\n       <input style=\"width:20%\" placeholder=\"enter your name\"type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" name=\"name\" value=\"\" v-model=\"name\">\r\n       <div> {{ name }} </div>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n          el: \'#app1\',\r\n    data: {\r\n            name: \'\'\r\n    }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',10,1,'VueJs v-model directive - nexladder','VueJs v-model - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522516946,'2018-03-31 17:22:26','2018-03-31 17:39:10'),(74,9,14,'VueJs v-pre','vuejs-v-pre-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>v-pre</strong> skip compilation for this element and all its children. You can use this for displaying raw mustache tags. skipping large numbers of nodes with no directives on them can also speed up compilation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the example</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;span v-pre>{{ name }}&lt;/span&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'Evan You\'</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>it will skip compilation and print the raw mustache tags.<code>v-pre</code> directive are used to increase the execution speed.</p>\r\n<p>if we remove the <code>v-pre</code> directive, it will print Evan You</p>\r\n</div> \r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app1\">\r\n       <span v-pre>{{ name }}</span>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n          el: \'#app1\',\r\n    data: {\r\n            name: \'Evan You\'\r\n    }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',11,1,'VueJs v-pre directive - nexladder','VueJs v-pre - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522517087,'2018-03-31 17:24:47','2018-03-31 17:36:25'),(75,9,14,'VueJs v-cloak','vuejs-v-cloak-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><strong>v-cloak</strong> will remain on the element until the associated Vue instance finishes compilation. This directive can be used to hide un-compiled mustache bindings until the Vue instance is ready.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pln\">[v-cloak]</span><span class=\"pun\"> {</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n	display</span><span class=\"pun\">:</span><span class=\"pln\">none</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n}</span></code></pre>\r\n<p>The <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> will not be visible until the <strong>compilation</strong> is done.</p>\r\n</div>',12,1,'VueJs v-cloak directive - nexladder','VueJs v-cloak - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522517156,'2018-03-31 17:25:56','2018-03-31 17:25:56'),(76,9,14,'VueJs v-once','vuejs-v-once-directive','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><strong>v-once</strong> render the element and component once only. On subsequent re-renders, the element/component and all its children will be treated as static content and skipped. This can be used to optimize update performance.</p>\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the example of without using <code>v-once</code></p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;div&gt;{{ name }}&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		 &lt;input type=\"button\" value=\"click me to change name\" v-on:click=\"name = \'Saarthak Singh\'\" class=\"btn-default\" /&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'Evan You\'</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app1\">\r\n       <div>{{ name }}</div>\r\n     <input type=\"button\" value=\"click me to change name\" v-on:click=\"name = \'Saarthak Singh\'\" class=\"btn-primary\" />\r\n     </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n          el: \'#app1\',\r\n    data: {\r\n            name: \'Evan You\'\r\n    }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',13,1,'VueJs v-once directive - nexladder','VueJs v-once - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522517240,'2018-03-31 17:27:20','2018-03-31 17:34:19'),(77,9,15,'VueJs Template','vuejs-template','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>Vue.js uses an HTML-based template syntax that allows you to declaratively bind the rendered DOM to the underlying Vue instance\'s data. All Vue.js templates are valid HTML that can be parsed by spec-compliant browsers and HTML parsers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the example</p>\r\n\r\n<p><pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"tag\">&lt;div id=\"vue_template\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;h2&gt;Name : {{name}}&lt;/h2></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;div v-text=\"html\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;div v-html=\"html\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>\r\n &lt;a v-bind:href=\"href\"&gt;Evan You&lt;/a&gt;<span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/div&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</p>\r\n  \r\n<p><pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"kwd\">Vue</span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#vue_template</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  data</span><span class=\"pun\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n         name</span><span class=\"pun\">: \"</span><span class=\"pln\">Evan You</span><span class=\"pun\">\",</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n	 html</span><span class=\"pun\">: \"</span><span class=\"pln\">&lt;h4&gt;Vue was created by Evan You&lt;/h4&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">\",</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n	 href</span><span class=\"pun\">: \"</span><span class=\"pln\">http://evanyou.me/</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n  }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n })</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</p>   \r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"vue_template\">\r\n <h2>Name : {{name}}</h2>\r\n <div v-text=\"html\"></div>\r\n <div v-html=\"html\"></div>\r\n <a v-bind:href=\"href\">Evan You</a>\r\n</div>\r\n<script>\r\nnew Vue({\r\n  el: \'#vue_template\', \r\n  data: {\r\n     name: \"Evan You\",\r\n   html: \"<h4>Vue was created by Evan You</h4>\",\r\n   href: \"http://evanyou.me/\"\r\n  }\r\n })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',14,1,'VueJs Template - nexladder','VueJs Template - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522518960,'2018-03-31 17:56:00','2018-03-31 17:59:36'),(78,9,16,'VueJs Component','vuejs-component','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><h2>Vue Components</h2> are one of the important features of VueJS that creates custom elements, which can be reused in HTML and they help you extend basic HTML elements to encapsulate reusable code.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"tag\">&lt;div id=\"component_test\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;testcomponent&gt;&lt;/testcomponent&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;div id=\"component_test1\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n  &lt;testcomponent&gt;&lt;/testcomponent&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\nVue</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\">component</span><span class=\"pun\">(\'</span><span class=\"str\">testcomponent</span><span class=\"pun\">\', {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  template </span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">&lt;div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;This is coming from component&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n});</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nvar </span><span class=\"pln\">vm </span><span class=\"pln\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pln\">Vue</span><span class=\"pln\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  el </span><span class=\"pln\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">#component_test</span><span class=\"pln\">\'</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n});</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nvar </span><span class=\"pln\">vm1 </span><span class=\"pln\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pln\">Vue</span><span class=\"pln\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  el </span><span class=\"pln\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">#component_test1</span><span class=\"pln\">\'</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n});</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/script&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"component_test\">\r\n    <testcomponent></testcomponent>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"component_test1\">\r\n  <testcomponent></testcomponent>\r\n</div>\r\n<script>\r\nVue.component(\'testcomponent\', {\r\n  template : \'<div><h3>This is coming from component</h3></div>\'\r\n});\r\nvar vm = new Vue({\r\n  el : \'#component_test\'\r\n});\r\nvar vm1 = new Vue({\r\n  el : \'#component_test1\'\r\n});\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h3>Components and Passing Data</h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re familiar with React or Angular, the idea of components and passing state won\'t be new to you. In case you\'re not, let\'s go through some of the main concepts.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pln\">Vue</span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">app_component</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  template</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">&lt;h1&gt;Hello VueJs&lt;/h1&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n})</span></code></pre>\r\n<p>This works, but isn\'t terribly useful as it can only be used once and we\'re not yet passing the information to different components. One way to pass data from a parent to a child is called <strong>props</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>:name</strong> in the HTML is a shortcut for Vue binding. Binding can be used for all kinds of things but in this instance, it keeps us from having to place the state in a mustache template, like this <code>{{ name }}</code>.\r\n<p>Below, Vue.component is the component, and new Vue is called the instance. You can have more than one instance in an application. Typically, we\'ll have one instance and several components, as the instance is the main app.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"tag\">&lt;div id=\"my_test_component\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;mycomponent :name=\"createby\"&gt;&lt;/mycomponent&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;div id=\"my_test_component1\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n  &lt;mycomponent :name=\"createby\"&gt;&lt;/mycomponent&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\nVue</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\">component</span><span class=\"pun\">(\'</span><span class=\"str\">mycomponent</span><span class=\"pun\">\', {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  template </span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">&lt;div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Component is created by {{ name }}&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  props</span><span class=\"pun\">: [\"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\"]</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n});</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nvar </span><span class=\"pln\">vm </span><span class=\"pln\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pln\">Vue</span><span class=\"pln\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  el </span><span class=\"pln\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">#my_test_component</span><span class=\"pln\">\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  data</span><span class=\"pun\">:</span><span class=\"pun\"> {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n    createby</span><span class=\"pun\">: \"</span><span class=\"pln\">Evan You</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n  }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n});</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nvar </span><span class=\"pln\">vm1 </span><span class=\"pln\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pln\">Vue</span><span class=\"pln\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  el </span><span class=\"pln\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">#my_test_component1</span><span class=\"pln\">\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n  data</span><span class=\"pun\">:</span><span class=\"pun\"> {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n    createby</span><span class=\"pun\">: \"</span><span class=\"pln\">Saarthak Singh</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n});</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/script&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<div id=\"my_test_component\">\r\n    <mycomponent :name=\"createby\"></mycomponent>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"my_test_component1\">\r\n  <mycomponent :name=\"createby\"></mycomponent>\r\n</div>\r\n<script>\r\nVue.component(\'mycomponent\', {\r\n  template : \'<div><h3>Component is created by {{ name }}</h3></div>\',\r\n  props: [\"name\"]\r\n});\r\nvar vm = new Vue({\r\n  el : \'#my_test_component\',\r\n  data: {\r\n    createby: \"Evan You\"\r\n  }\r\n});\r\nvar vm1 = new Vue({\r\n  el : \'#my_test_component1\',\r\n  data: {\r\n    createby: \"Saarthak Singh\"\r\n }\r\n});\r\n</script>\r\n</div>',15,1,'VueJs Component - nexladder','VueJs Component - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522519442,'2018-03-31 18:04:02','2018-04-03 02:31:23'),(79,9,16,'VueJs Transition','vuejs-transition','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><code>transition</code> serve as transition effects for single element/component. The <transition> only applies the transition behavior to the wrapped content inside; it doesnât render an extra DOM element, or show up in the inspected component hierarchy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the example</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"tag\">&lt;div id=\"vue_transition\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n  &lt;button v-on:click = \"show = !show\"&gt;Click Me&lt;/button&gt;</span>&lt;br /&gt;<span class=\"tag\">\r\n  &lt;transition name = \"fade\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n  &lt;p v-show=\"show\" v-bind:style=\"styleobj\">My Animation Using VueJs&lt;/p&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/transition&gt;<span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/div&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"vue_transition\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;button v-on:click = \"show = !show\"&gt;Click Me&lt;/button&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n		  &lt;transition name = \"fade\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n		  &lt;p v-show=\"show\" v-bind:style=\"styleObj\">My First Animation Using VueJs&lt;/p&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n		 &lt;/transition&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#vue_transition</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		          show</span><span class=\"pln\"> : </span><span class=\"str\">true</span><span class=\"pln\">,</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			  styleObj</span><span class=\"pun\"> : </span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			    {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			       fontSize</span><span class=\"pun\"> : \'</span><span class=\"str\">24px</span><span class=\"pun\">\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			       color</span><span class=\"pun\"> : \'</span><span class=\"str\">#888</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			    }</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		       },</span><span class=\"pun\"><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		 methods</span><span class=\"pun\"> : {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			   }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	})</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;style&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n      .fade-enter-active, .fade-leave-active</span><span class=\"pun\"> { </span><span class=\"str\">\r\n	      transition:opacity 1s</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n      }</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n     .fade-enter, .fade-leave-to </span><span class=\"pun\">{</span><span class=\"str\">\r\n	      opacity:0</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n       }</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n  &lt;/style&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"vue_transition\">\r\n       <button v-on:click = \"show = !show\">Click Me</button><br />\r\n      <transition name = \"fade\">\r\n      <p v-show=\"show\" v-bind:style=\"styleObj\">My First Animation Using VueJs</p>\r\n     </transition>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n          el: \'#vue_transition\',\r\n    data: {\r\n              show : true,\r\n        styleObj : \r\n          {\r\n             fontSize : \'24px\',\r\n             color : \'#888\'\r\n          }\r\n           },\r\n     methods : {\r\n         }\r\n  })\r\n   </script>\r\n   <style>\r\n      .fade-enter-active, .fade-leave-active { \r\n        transition:opacity 1s\r\n      }\r\n     .fade-enter, .fade-leave-to {\r\n        opacity:0\r\n       }\r\n  </style>\r\n</div>',16,1,'VueJs Transition - nexladder','VueJs Transition - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522519579,'2018-03-31 18:06:19','2018-03-31 18:10:10'),(80,9,17,'VueJs Watch','vuejs-watch','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>It is most useful when you want to perform asynchronous or expensive operations in response to changing data. Keep in mind watchers only change when that specific data property changes. </p>\r\n<p>In this topic, we\'ll learn about the Watch property. <i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below the example, we\'ll see we can use it.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"watch\"&gt;\r\n	     &lt;input type=\"text\" v-model=\"meter\" placeholder=\"meter\" /&gt;\r\n	     &lt;input type=\"text\" v-model=\"cm\" placeholder=\"cm\" /&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#watch</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		          meter</span><span class=\"pln\"> : \'\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			  cm</span><span class=\"pun\"> : \'\',</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		       },</span><span class=\"pun\"><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		 methods</span><span class=\"pun\"> : {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			   },</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		 watch</span><span class=\"pun\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			  meter</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"kwd\">function</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">val</span><span class=\"pun\">)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n				  {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n				        this.meter </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"pln\">val</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n					this.cm </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"pln\">val * 100</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n				  }, </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			  cm</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"kwd\">function</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">val</span><span class=\"pun\">)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n				   {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n				          this.meter </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"pln\">val / 100</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n					  this.cm </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"pln\">val</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n				   }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			}</span><span class=\"pun\">	   \r\n	})</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n<p>Above, we\'ve created two textboxes, one for meter and second for centimeters. In data property, the meter and cm are initialized to empty. There is a watch object created with two functions meter and cm. In both the functions, the conversion from meter to cm and vice-versa.</p>\r\n<p>We enter values inside any of the texboxes, whichever is changed, Watch takes care of updating both the textboxes. We don\'t have to specially assign any events and wait for it to change and do the extra work of validating. Watch takes care of updating the textboxes with the calculation done in the respective functions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"watch\">\r\n       <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" style=\"width:25%\" v-model=\"meter\" placeholder=\"meter\" />\r\n       <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" style=\"width:25%\" v-model=\"cm\" placeholder=\"cm\" />\r\n     </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n          el: \'#watch\',\r\n    data: {\r\n              meter : \'\',\r\n        cm : \'\',\r\n           },\r\n     methods : {\r\n         },\r\n     watch: {\r\n        meter: function(val)\r\n          {\r\n                this.meter = val;\r\n          this.cm = val * 100;\r\n          }, \r\n        cm: function(val)\r\n           {\r\n                  this.meter = val / 100;\r\n            this.cm = val;\r\n           }\r\n      }    \r\n  })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',17,1,'VueJs Watch - nexladder','VueJs Watch - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522520087,'2018-03-31 18:14:47','2018-03-31 18:18:20'),(81,9,18,'VueJs Router','vuejs-router','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>VueJS does not have a built-in router feauture. We need to follow some additional steps to install it.</p>\r\n<p>Direct Download from CDN</p>\r\n<p>The latest version of vue-router is available at <a href=\"https://unpkg.com/vue-router/dist/vue-router.js\">https://unpkg.com/vue-router/dist/vue-router.js</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://unpkg.com/vue-router/dist/vue-router.js?v=1\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n      &lt;p>\r\n       &lt;router-link to = \"/route1\"&gt;Page 1&lt;/router-link&gt; | \r\n       &lt;router-link to = \"/route2\"&gt;Page 2&lt;/router-link&gt;\r\n      &lt;/p&gt;\r\n     &lt;router-view&gt;&lt;/router-view&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\"> \r\n const </span><span class=\"pln\">route1 </span><span class=\"pun\">= {</span><span class=\"str\">template </span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">&lt;div&gt;Page 1&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">\' }</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n const </span><span class=\"pln\">route2 </span><span class=\"pun\">= {</span><span class=\"str\">template </span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"pln\">&lt;div&gt;Page 2&lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"pun\">\' }</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n const </span><span class=\"pln\">routes </span><span class=\"pun\">= [</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n    {</span><span class=\"pln\">path</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'/</span><span class=\"pln\">route1</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">component</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"pln\">route1</span><span class=\"pun\"> }, </span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n    {</span><span class=\"pln\">path</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'/</span><span class=\"pln\">route2</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">component</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"pln\">route2</span><span class=\"pun\"> }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n  ];</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n const </span><span class=\"pln\">router </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pln\">VueRouter</span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n    routes</span><span class=\"com\"> // short for `routes: routes`</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n });</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n var </span><span class=\"pln\">vm </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"pln\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n   el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n   router, </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n   data</span><span class=\"pun\">:</span><span class=\"pun\"> {</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n   }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n });</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>The router-link is what we use to generate the links, with \"to\" we set the path. the router-view, as the comment in the code says is the place where the routed component is going to render.</p>\r\n<p>First we set a couple of vuejs components (route1 and route2) so we have something to bind the routes to.</p>\r\n<p>Then we create the routes object with three paths configurations:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"points\">\r\n    <li>The first path (\"route1\"), renders the route1 component.</li>\r\n    <li>The second path (\"route2\"), renders the route2 component.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The VueRouter constructor takes the routes as the param. The router object is assigned to the main vue instance using the following piece of code.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<script src=\" https://unpkg.com/vue-router/dist/vue-router.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app1\">\r\n      <p>\r\n       <router-link to = \"/route1\">Page 1</router-link> | \r\n       <router-link to = \"/route2\">Page 2</router-link>\r\n      </p>\r\n     <router-view></router-view>\r\n</div>\r\n<script> \r\n const route1 = {template : \'<div>Page 1</div>\' }\r\n const route2 = {template : \'<div>Page 2</div>\' }\r\n const routes = [\r\n    {path: \'/route1\', component: route1 }, \r\n    {path: \'/route2\', component: route2 }\r\n  ];\r\n const router = new VueRouter({\r\n    routes // short for `routes: routes`\r\n });\r\n var vm = new Vue ({\r\n   el: \'#app1\', \r\n   router, \r\n   data: {\r\n   }\r\n });\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',18,1,'VueJs Router - nexladder','VueJs Router - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522520506,'2018-03-31 18:21:46','2018-04-04 00:54:22'),(82,9,17,'VueJs Computed Properties','vuejs-computed-properties','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><strong>Computed properties</strong> are typically dependent on other data properties. They behave exactly like the language standard <code>get</code>/<code>set</code> properties. Any change to the dependent properties will trigger the logic for the computed property.Computed properties are cached based on their dependencies so they\'ll only rerun if a dependency changes. (for ex; a computed property that returns a <code>new Date()</code> will never return because the logic will never run more than 1 time).</p>\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n	 &lt;div&gt;Here Random number Coming from Method: {{ getRandomNumberByMethod() }}&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	 &lt;div&gt;Here Random number Coming from Computed: {{ getRandomNumberByComputed }}&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	 &lt;div&gt;Here Random number Coming from Computed: {{ getRandomNumberByComputed }}&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	 &lt;div&gt;Here Random number Coming from Method: {{ getRandomNumberByMethod() }}&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	 &lt;div&gt;Here Random number Coming from Method: {{ getRandomNumberByMethod() }}&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	 &lt;div&gt;Here Random number Coming from Computed: {{ getRandomNumberByComputed }}&lt;/div&gt;\r\n    &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n			data</span><span class=\"pln\">:</span><span class=\"pln\">{</span><span class=\"pln\"><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			},</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			methods</span><span class=\"pun\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			  getRandomNumberByMethod</span><span class=\"pun\">:<span class=\"str\"></span>function<span class=\"pun\">() {</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n			      return </span><span class=\"pln\">Math.random()</span><span class=\"pln\">;</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			  },</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			},</span><span class=\"pun\">computed</span><span class=\"pun\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			  getRandomNumberByComputed</span><span class=\"pun\">:<span class=\"str\"></span>function<span class=\"pun\">() {</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n			      return </span><span class=\"pln\">Math.random()</span><span class=\"pln\">;</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			  },</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"app\">\r\n    <div>Here Random number Coming from Method: <strong>{{ getRandomNumberByMethod() }}</strong></div>\r\n    <div>Here Random number Coming from Computed: <strong>{{ getRandomNumberByComputed }}</strong></div>\r\n    <div>Here Random number Coming from Computed: <strong>{{ getRandomNumberByComputed }}</strong></div>\r\n    <div>Here Random number Coming from Method: <strong>{{ getRandomNumberByMethod() }}</strong></div>\r\n    <div>Here Random number Coming from Method: <strong>{{ getRandomNumberByMethod() }}</strong></div>\r\n    <div>Here Random number Coming from Computed: <strong>{{ getRandomNumberByComputed }}</strong></div>\r\n    </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n          el: \'#app\',\r\n      data:{\r\n      },\r\n      methods: {\r\n        getRandomNumberByMethod:function() {\r\n            return Math.random();\r\n        },\r\n      },computed: {\r\n        getRandomNumberByComputed:function() {\r\n            return Math.random();\r\n        },\r\n      }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p>Above code, we\'ve created a method <code>getRandomNumberByMethod()</code> and a computed property with a function <code>getRandomNumberByComputed</code>.Both are returning a random numbers using <code>Math.random()</code>.</p> \r\n <p>In above code, we\'ll see that random numbers returned from the computed property remains the same irrespective of the number of times it is called while <code>getRandomNumberByMethod()</code> returns a different value everytime it is called</p>\r\n</div>',17,1,'VueJs Computed Properties - nexladder','VueJs Computed Properties - Learn VueJs, Tutorial VueJs, VueJs Tutorial, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522722876,'2018-04-03 02:34:36','2018-04-04 00:45:30'),(83,9,19,'VueJs Axios','vuejs-axios-rest-api','<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p><strong>Axios</strong> is a great http client library for making Ajax requests. It\'s also quite easy to use with Vue. It uses promises by default and runs on both the client and the server (which makes it appropriate for fetching data during server-side rendering). It provides a simple and rich API. You can combine it with <code>async/await</code>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://unpkg.com/axios/dist/axios.min.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"axios\"&gt;\r\n	   &lt;p v-if=\"this.users.length ==0\"&gt;loading...&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	   &lt;ul&gt;\r\n		 &lt;li v-for=\"user in users\"&gt;{{ user.name }}&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	   &lt;/ul&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#axios</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		          users</span><span class=\"pln\"> : </span><span class=\"pun\">[]</span><span class=\"pln\">,</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		          url</span><span class=\"pln\"> : \'</span><span class=\"str\">https://nexladder.com/users.json</span><span class=\"pln\">\',</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		       },</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n	   created</span><span class=\"pun\">() {</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n		           var </span><span class=\"pln\">vm </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">this</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n			   axios</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"kwd\">get</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"kwd\">this</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\">url</span><span class=\"pun\">)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			   .</span><span class=\"pln\">then</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">function</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">response</span><span class=\"pun\">) {</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n			      vm</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\">users</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"pln\">response</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\">data</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			   })</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		    }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://unpkg.com/axios/dist/axios.min.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n<div id=\"axios\">\r\n	   <p v-if=\"this.users.length ==0\">loading...</p>\r\n	   <ul>\r\n		 <li v-for=\"user in users\">{{ user.name }}</li>\r\n	   </ul>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n        	el: \'#axios\',\r\n		data: {\r\n		          users : [],\r\n		          url : \'https://nexladder.com/users.json\',\r\n		       },\r\n	   created() {\r\n		           var vm = this;\r\n			   axios.get(this.url)\r\n			   .then(function(response) {\r\n			      vm.users=response.data\r\n			   })\r\n		    }\r\n             })\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',20,1,'VueJs Axios Rest Api - nexladder','VueJs Axios, VueJs Rest APIs, VueJs Ajax Request, VueJs Http Request, VueJs Ajax Request in Vuejs, Learn VueJs Online, VueJs Tutorial for Beginners, Learn VueJs Easily, VueJs Course Online, Online VueJs Course, VueJs Online Course, VueJs Training, Learn VueJs with Example, Learning VueJs, Online VueJs.','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522803704,'2018-04-04 01:01:44','2018-04-04 01:03:52'),(84,9,20,'VueJs Filters','vuejs-filters','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>In VueJs, you can register your filters in two different ways: <strong>Globally</strong> and <strong>Locally</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Filters are JavaScript functions, they take the value to be transformed as the first parameter, but you can also pass in as many other arguments as you will need to return the formatted version of that value.</p>\r\n<h2>VueJs Global Filters</h2>\r\n<p>Here is what a Global filter looks like:</p>\r\n<p><i><strong>Note:</strong> The filter definition must always be above the main Vue instance.</i></p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"tag\">&lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\nVue</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\">filter</span><span class=\"pun\">(\'</span><span class=\"str\">toUSD</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pln\">function</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">value</span><span class=\"pun\">) {</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n  return </span><span class=\"pun\">`</span><span class=\"pun\">$${</span><span class=\"pln\">value</span><span class=\"pun\">}`;</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n});</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/script&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		        price</span><span class=\"pun\">: </span><span class=\"tag\">5000</span><span class=\"pun\"></span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n             })</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;div id=\"app\"&gt;\r\n      &lt;span&gt;{{ price | toUSD }}&lt;/span&gt;\r\n   &lt;/div&gt;<span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1\"></script>\r\n   <div id=\"app\">\r\n      <span>{{ price | toUSD }}</span>\r\n   </div>\r\n<script>\r\n\r\nVue.filter(\'toUSD\', function(value) {\r\n  return `$${value}`;\r\n});\r\n	new Vue ({\r\n		el: \'#app\',\r\n		data: {\r\n		        price: 5000\r\n		}\r\n	})\r\n   </script>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>VueJs Local Filters</h2>\r\n<p>Here is what a Local filter looks like:</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;\r\n   &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;div id=\"app1\"&gt;\r\n       &lt;span&gt;{{ price | toUSD }}&lt;/span&gt;\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n     &lt;script&gt;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n     new </span><span class=\"pun\">Vue </span><span class=\"pun\">({</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        	el</span><span class=\"pun\">: \'</span><span class=\"str\">#app</span><span class=\"pun\">\',<span class=\"pln\">\r\n		data</span><span class=\"pln\">: {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		     price</span><span class=\"pln\"> : </span><span class=\"pln\">1500,</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		},</span><span class=\"pun\"><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		 filters</span><span class=\"pun\"> : {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n		                 toUSD</span><span class=\"pun\"> : </span><span class=\"kwd\">function</span><span class=\"pun\">(value) {</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n			                return</span><span class=\"pun\"> `$${</span><span class=\"pln\">value</span><span class=\"pun\">}`</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n			          }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n		             }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	})</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n   &lt;/script&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\"></span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Output</p>\r\n<div id=\"app1\">\r\n   <span>{{ price | toUSD }}</span>\r\n</div>\r\n     <script>\r\n     new Vue ({\r\n        	el: \'#app1\',\r\n		data: {\r\n		     price : 1500,\r\n		},\r\n		 filters : {\r\n		                 toUSD : function(value) {\r\n			                return `$${value}`\r\n			          }\r\n		             }\r\n	})\r\n   </script>\r\n</div>',21,1,'VueJs Filters - nexladder','VueJs Filters global, local - Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more','Learn VUEJS in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example such as vuejs declarative rendering, vuejs conditionals and loops, vuejs handling user input, vuejs conditional and loops, vuejs two way data binding, vuejs events, vuejs component, vuejs template, vuejs router, vuejs directive and more',1,1522805601,'2018-04-04 01:33:21','2018-04-04 01:44:49'),(85,10,21,'JSON Overview','json-overview','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<ul class=\"points\">\r\n  <h3>Advantages of JSON</h3>\r\n  <li>Square brackets<code>[]</code> store arrays and values are separated by <code>,</code>(comma).</li>\r\n  <li>Curly braces<code>{}</code> store objects and each name is followed by <code>:</code>(colon), the name/value pairs are separated by <code>,</code> (comma).</li>\r\n  <li>Data is represented in name/value pairs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"pun\">{</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n   \"</span><span class=\"str\">fruits</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\">: [</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n        {</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	  \"</span><span class=\"pln\">id</span><span class=\"pun\">\" : \"</span><span class=\"str\">1</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\">,</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	  \"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\" : \"</span><span class=\"str\">Apple</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\">,</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	  \"</span><span class=\"pln\">quantity</span><span class=\"pun\">\" : \"</span><span class=\"str\">10</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\"></span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	},</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	{</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	  \"</span><span class=\"pln\">id</span><span class=\"pun\">\" : \"</span><span class=\"str\">2</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\">,</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	  \"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\" : \"</span><span class=\"str\">Banana</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	  \"</span><span class=\"pln\">quantity</span><span class=\"pun\">\" : \"</span><span class=\"str\">12</span><span class=\"pun\">\"</span><span class=\"pun\"></span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n	}</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n   ]</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n }</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>',1,1,'JSON Overview - nexladder','Json Overview - Learn JSON, Tutorial JSON, JSON Tutorial, Learn JSON Online, JSON Tutorial for Beginners, Learn JSON Easily, JSON MySql Tutorial, JSON Course Online, Online JSON Course, JSON Online Course, JSON Training, Learn JSON with Example, Learning JSON, Online JSON.','Learn JSON in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example, enables you to create dynamic web pages and learn how JSON can help you develop various web applications.',1,1522976199,'2018-04-06 00:56:39','2018-04-06 00:56:39'),(86,10,21,'JSON Data Types','json-data-types','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>JSON format supports the following data types:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"points\">\r\n	<li>Number</li>\r\n	<li>String</li>\r\n	<li>Array</li>\r\n	<li>Object</li>\r\n	<li>Boolean</li>\r\n	<li>NULL</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>JSON Number</h2>\r\n<p>In JSON, Number must be integer or a floating point.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pun\">{\"</span><span class=\"pln\">age</span><span class=\"pun\">\":</span><span class=\"str\">10</span><span class=\"pun\">}</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>JSON String</h2>\r\n<p>In JSON, String must be in double quotes <code>\"\"</code>.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pun\">{\"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\":\"</span><span class=\"str\">Saarthak Singh</span><span class=\"pun\">\"}</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>JSON Object</h2>\r\n<p>In JSON, Values can be objects.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pun\">{\"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\":\"</span><span class=\"str\">Saarthak Singh</span><span class=\"pun\">\", \"</span><span class=\"pln\">age</span><span class=\"pun\">\":</span><span class=\"pln\">10</span><span class=\"pun\">, \"</span><span class=\"str\">Country</span><span class=\"str\">\":\"</span><span class=\"str\">India</span><span class=\"pun\">\"}</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>JSON Arrays</h2>\r\n<p>Values in JSON can be arrays.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pun\">{\"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\":[\"</span><span class=\"str\">Saarthak Singh</span><span class=\"pun\">\", \"</span><span class=\"str\">Vijay Singh</span><span class=\"pun\">\"]</span><span class=\"pun\">}</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>JSON Booleans</h2>\r\n<p>Values in JSON can be true/false.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pun\">{\"</span><span class=\"pln\">status</span><span class=\"pun\">\":</span><span class=\"str\">true</span><span class=\"pun\">}</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>JSON NULL</h2>\r\n<p>Values in JSON can be null.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pun\">{\"</span><span class=\"pln\">Address2</span><span class=\"pun\">\":</span><span class=\"str\">null</span><span class=\"pun\">}</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>',2,1,'JSON Data Types - nexladder','Json Data Types - Learn JSON, Tutorial JSON, JSON Tutorial, Learn JSON Online, JSON Tutorial for Beginners, Learn JSON Easily, JSON MySql Tutorial, JSON Course Online, Online JSON Course, JSON Online Course, JSON Training, Learn JSON with Example, Learning JSON, Online JSON.','Learn JSON in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example, enables you to create dynamic web pages and learn how JSON can help you develop various web applications.',1,1522976309,'2018-04-06 00:58:29','2018-06-09 02:07:42'),(87,10,21,'JSON Objects','json-objects','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>JSON Objects</strong> are written with <code>key/value</code> pairs and surrounded by curly braces<code>{}</code> and keys and values are separated by colon <code>:</code> and each <code>key/value</code> pair is separated by a comma <code>,</code>.</p>\r\n  <p>We can access the object values by using dot <code>.</code> notation and also access by using brackets <code>[]</code> notation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Below an example to <strong>create an empty object</strong>.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">var </span><span class=\"pln\">jsonObj </span><span class=\"pun\">= {};</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Example #1</strong>.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">var </span><span class=\"pln\">jsonObj </span><span class=\"pun\">= {\"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\":\"</span><span class=\"str\">Saarthak Singh</span><span class=\"pun\">\",\"</span><span class=\"pln\">age</span><span class=\"pun\">\":\"</span><span class=\"str\">20</span><span class=\"pun\">\"}</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>Access a JSON object using dot <code>.</code> notation:</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pln\">jsonObj</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"com\"> // Saarthak Singh</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>Access a JSON object using bracket <code>[]</code> notation:</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"pln\">jsonObj</span><span class=\"pun\">[\"</span><span class=\"pln\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">\"]</span><span class=\"com\"> // Saarthak Singh</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>',3,1,'JSON Objects - nexladder','Json Objects - Learn JSON, Tutorial JSON, JSON Tutorial, Learn JSON Online, JSON Tutorial for Beginners, Learn JSON Easily, JSON MySql Tutorial, JSON Course Online, Online JSON Course, JSON Online Course, JSON Training, Learn JSON with Example, Learning JSON, Online JSON.','Learn JSON in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example, enables you to create dynamic web pages and learn how JSON can help you develop various web applications.',1,1522976419,'2018-04-06 01:00:19','2018-04-06 01:01:42'),(88,10,21,'JSON Arrays','json-arrays','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p><strong>JSON Arrays</strong> are alomost similar to the arrays in javascript.</p>\r\n  <p>JSON array values <strong>must be type</strong> number, array, object, boolean and null.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> #Example</p>\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">var </span><span class=\"pln\">fruitsObj </span><span class=\"pun\">= {\"</span><span class=\"pln\">fruits</span><span class=\"pun\">\" : [\"</span><span class=\"str\">Apple</span><span class=\"pun\">\",\"</span><span class=\"str\">Mango</span><span class=\"pun\">\",\"</span><span class=\"str\">Banana</span><span class=\"pun\">\"]};</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nfor </span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">index </span><span class=\"kwd\">in </span><span class=\"pun\">fruitsObj.fruits</span><span class=\"pun\">) {</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n   console</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"kwd\">log</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">fruitsObj</span><span class=\"pun\">.</span><span class=\"pln\">fruits</span><span class=\"pun\">[</span><span class=\"pln\">index</span><span class=\"pun\">]</span><span class=\"pun\">);</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n }</span>\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<img src=\"https://nexladder.com/uploads/json arrray.png\" alt=\"json array\" class=\"img-responsive\" />\r\n</div>',4,1,'JSON Arrays - nexladder','Json Arrays - Learn JSON, Tutorial JSON, JSON Tutorial, Learn JSON Online, JSON Tutorial for Beginners, Learn JSON Easily, JSON MySql Tutorial, JSON Course Online, Online JSON Course, JSON Online Course, JSON Training, Learn JSON with Example, Learning JSON, Online JSON.','Learn JSON in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example, enables you to create dynamic web pages and learn how JSON can help you develop various web applications.',1,1522976590,'2018-04-06 01:03:10','2018-04-06 01:05:55'),(89,10,21,'PHP JSON','php-json-example','<div class=\"content\">\r\n   <p>PHP allows us to encode and decode JSON by using <code>json_encode()</code> and <code>json_decode</code> functions.</p>\r\n   <ul class=\"points\">\r\n     <li>json_encode - Returns the JSON representation of a value</li>\r\n     <li>json_decode - Decodes a JSON string</li>\r\n   </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>json_encode</h2>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"str\">string</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span> <span class=\"kwd\">json_encode</span><span class=\"pun\"> (</span><span class=\"str\"> mixed </span><span class=\"pln\">$value</span> <span class=\"pun\"> [,</span><span class=\"str\"> int</span><span class=\"pln\"> $options</span><span class=\"pun\"> =</span><span class=\"pun\"> 0</span><span class=\"pun\">[,</span><span class=\"str\">int </span><span class=\"pln\">$depth </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"pln\">512</span><span class=\"pun\">]])</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>Let\'s see the example to encode JSON.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"pun\">&lt;?php</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n $array </span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"pln\"> array</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"str\">a</span><span class=\"pun\">\' => \'</span><span class=\"str\">Apple</span><span class=\"pun\">\', </span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"str\">b</span><span class=\"pun\">\' => \'</span><span class=\"str\">Mango</span><span class=\"pun\">\', \'</span><span class=\"str\">c</span><span class=\"pun\">\' => \'</span><span class=\"str\">Banana</span><span class=\"pun\">\', \'</span><span class=\"str\">d</span><span class=\"pun\">\' => \'</span><span class=\"str\">Apricot</span><span class=\"pun\">\', \'</span><span class=\"str\">e</span><span class=\"pun\">\' => \'</span><span class=\"str\">Blackberry</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pun\">);</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n echo </span><span class=\"str\">json_encode</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">$array</span><span class=\"pun\">);</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n?></span></code></pre>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"code\"><pre><strong>Output:</strong> {\"a\":\"Apple\",\"b\":\"Mango\",\"c\":\"Banana\",\"d\":\"Apricot\",\"e\":\"Blackberry\"}</pre></div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2>json_decode</h2>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"str\">mixed</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span> <span class=\"kwd\">json_decode</span><span class=\"pun\"> (</span><span class=\"str\"> string </span><span class=\"pln\">$json</span> <span class=\"pun\"> [,</span><span class=\"str\"> bool</span><span class=\"pln\"> $assoc</span><span class=\"pun\"> =</span><span class=\"pun\"> false </span><span class=\"pun\">[,</span><span class=\"str\">int </span><span class=\"pln\">$depth </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"pln\">512</span><span class=\"pun\"> [,</span><span class=\"str\"> int</span><span class=\"pln\"> $options</span><span class=\"pun\"> =</span><span class=\"pun\"> 0</span><span class=\"pun\">]]])</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>Let\'s see the example to decode JSON.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"pun\">&lt;?php</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n $str </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"str\">\'{\"a\":\"Apple\",\"b\":\"Mango\",\"c\":\"Banana\",\"d\":\"Apricot\",\"e\":\"Blackberry\"}\';</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n var_dump</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"str\">json_decode</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">$str</span><span class=\"pun\">));</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n?></span></code></pre>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"code\"><pre><strong>Output:</strong> object(stdClass)#1 (5) { [\"a\"]=> string(5) \"Apple\" [\"b\"]=> string(5) \"Mango\" [\"c\"]=> string(6) \"Banana\" [\"d\"]=> string(7) \"Apricot\" [\"e\"]=> string(10) \"Blackberry\" }</pre></div>\r\n\r\n</div>',5,1,'PHP Json Example - nexladder','Php Json Example - Learn JSON, Tutorial JSON, JSON Tutorial, Learn JSON Online, JSON Tutorial for Beginners, Learn JSON Easily, JSON MySql Tutorial, JSON Course Online, Online JSON Course, JSON Online Course, JSON Training, Learn JSON with Example, Learning JSON, Online JSON.','Learn JSON in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example, enables you to create dynamic web pages and learn how JSON can help you develop various web applications.',1,1522976977,'2018-04-06 01:09:37','2018-05-05 14:53:55'),(90,4,22,'Ajax Technologies','ajax-technologies','<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p>It is used in combination with other technologies, we\'ve discussed earlier</p>  \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p><strong>DOM</strong>: It represents the structure of XML and HTML documents and it is used for dynamic display and interaction with data.</p>  \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p><strong>XML or JSON</strong>: For carrying data to and from server. JSON (Javascript Object Notation) is like XML but short and faster than XML.</p>  \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p><strong>XMLHttpRequest</strong>: JavaScript object that performs <strong>asynchronous</strong> interaction with the server.</p>  \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p><strong>JavaScript</strong>: For asynchronous communication between client and server.</p>  \r\n <ul class=\"points\">\r\n   <li>Independently, it is used mainly for client-side validation.</li>\r\n   <li>Loosely typed scripting language..</li>\r\n   <li>JavaScript function is called when an event occurs in a page.</li>\r\n </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p>HTML/XHTML and CSS</p>  \r\n <p>It is used for displaying content, style and mainly used for presentation.</p>\r\n</div>',1,1,'Ajax Technologies - nexladder','Ajax Technologies - Learn Ajax, Tutorial Ajax, Ajax Tutorial, Learn Ajax Online, Ajax Tutorial for Beginners, Learn Ajax Easily, Ajax Course Online, Online Ajax Course, Ajax Online Course, Ajax Training, Learn Ajax with Example, Learning Ajax, Online Ajax.','Learn Ajax in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example.',1,1523168117,'2018-04-08 06:15:17','2018-04-08 06:15:17'),(91,4,22,'Ajax XMLHttpRequest','what-is-xmlhttprequest','<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p><strong>XMLHttpRequest (XHR)</strong>: It is used for <strong>asynchronous</strong> communication between client and server and send HTTP or HTTPS requests to a web server and load the server response data back into the script.</p>  \r\n <p>It performs following operations:</p>\r\n <ul class=\"points\">\r\n   <li>Updates the webpage without reloading it.</li>\r\n   <li>Receive data from a server - after the page has loaded.</li>\r\n   <li>Send data to a server - in the background.</li>\r\n </ul> \r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><strong>Create an XMLHttpRequest Object</strong></p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">var </span><span class=\"pln\">xmlHttpRqst </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"str\">XMLHttpRequest</span><span class=\"pun\">();</span><span class=\"com\"> For All modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, IE7+, Edge, Safari, Opera) </span></code></pre>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">var </span><span class=\"pln\">xmlHttpRqst </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"kwd\">new </span><span class=\"str\">ActiveXObject</span><span class=\"pun\">(\"</span><span class=\"str\">Microsoft.XMLHTTP</span><span class=\"pun\">\");</span><span class=\"com\"> For IE5 and IE6</span></code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p><h2>XMLHttpRequest Methods</h2>\r\n <table class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n		<tbody>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>new XMLHttpRequest()</td>\r\n				<td>Creates a new XMLHttpRequest object</td>\r\n			</tr>			\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>abort()</td>\r\n				<td>Cancels the current request</td>\r\n			</tr>			\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>getAllResponseHeaders()</td>\r\n				<td>Returns header information</td>\r\n			</tr>			\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>getResponseHeader()</td>\r\n				<td>Returns specific header information</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>open(method, url, async, user, password)</td>\r\n				<td><p>method: the request type GET or POST</p>\r\n						<p>url: the file location</p>\r\n						<p>async: true (asynchronous) or false (synchronous)</p>\r\n						<p>user: optional user name</p>\r\n						<p>password: optional password</p>\r\n				</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>send()</td>\r\n				<td>Sends the GET request.</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>send(string)</td>\r\n				<td>Sends the POST request.</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>setRequestHeader()</td>\r\n				<td>It adds request headers.</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n		</tbody>\r\n	</table>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><strong>Properties of XMLHttpRequest object</strong> are as follows:</p>\r\n    <table class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n		<tbody>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>onReadyStateChange</td>\r\n				<td>It is called whenever readystate attribute changes. It must not be used with synchronous requests.</td>\r\n			</tr>			\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>readyState</td>\r\n				<td><p>represents the state of the request. It ranges from 0 to 4.</p>\r\n					<p><strong>0</strong> : request not initialized</p>\r\n					<p><strong>1</strong> : server connection established</p>\r\n					<p><strong>2</strong> : request received</p>\r\n					<p><strong>3</strong> : processing request</p>\r\n					<p><strong>4</strong> : request finished and response is ready </p>\r\n				</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>reponseText</td>\r\n				<td>returns response as text.</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>responseXML</td>\r\n				<td>returns response as XML.</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>status</td>\r\n				<td><p>Returns the status-number of a request.</p>\r\n					<p><strong>200</strong> : \"OK\"</p>\r\n					<p><strong>403</strong> : \"Forbidden\"</p>\r\n					<p><strong>404</strong> : \"Not Found\"</p>\r\n					<p>...</p>\r\n				</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td>statusText</td>\r\n				<td>Returns the status-text (e.g. \"OK\" or \"Not Found\")</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n		</tbody>\r\n	</table>\r\n</div>',2,1,'Ajax XMLHttpRequest - nexladder','Ajax XMLHttpRequest - Learn Ajax, Tutorial Ajax, Ajax Tutorial, Learn Ajax Online, Ajax Tutorial for Beginners, Learn Ajax Easily, Ajax Course Online, Online Ajax Course, Ajax Online Course, Ajax Training, Learn Ajax with Example, Learning Ajax, Online Ajax.','Learn Ajax in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example.',1,1523168293,'2018-04-08 06:18:13','2018-04-08 06:18:13'),(92,4,22,'Ajax Advantages/Disadvantages','ajax-advantages-disadvantages','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <h2>Advantages of AJAX</h2>\r\n  <ul class=\"points\">\r\n    <li>Reduce the traffic travels between the client and the server.</li>\r\n    <li>AJAX make asynchronous calls to a web server. This means client browsers are avoid waiting for all data arrive before start the rendering.</li>\r\n    <li>AJAX communicates over HTTP Protocol.</li>\r\n    <li>No require to completely reload page again. AJAX is improve the speed and performance.</li>\r\n    <li>Response time is faster so increases performance and speed..</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <h2>Disadvantages of AJAX</h2>\r\n  <ul class=\"points\">\r\n    <li>Security is less in AJAX application as all files are downloaded at client side.</li>\r\n    <li>JavaScript disabled browsers cannot use the application.</li>\r\n    <li>More complex than building classic web application.</li>\r\n    <li>Ssearch engines would not be able to index an AJAX application.</li>\r\n    <li>Anyone can view the code source written for AJAX.</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n</div>',3,1,'Ajax Advantages/Disadvantages - nexladder','Ajax Advantages/Disadvantages - Learn Ajax, Tutorial Ajax, Ajax Tutorial, Learn Ajax Online, Ajax Tutorial for Beginners, Learn Ajax Easily, Ajax Course Online, Online Ajax Course, Ajax Online Course, Ajax Training, Learn Ajax with Example, Learning Ajax, Online Ajax.','Learn Ajax in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with example.',1,1523168417,'2018-04-08 06:20:17','2018-04-08 06:20:17'),(93,4,22,'Ajax Get Method Example','ajax-get-method-example-using-php','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"default prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class