ng <code>&lt;tagname&gt;</code> and a closing tag <code>&lt;/tagname&gt;</code>. HTML tag contains three main parts: opening tag, content, closing tag (&lt;tagname&gt;Content goes here...&lt;/tagname&gt;) For example, <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> has its closing tag <code>&lt;/html&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;title&gt;</code> tag has its closing tag <code>&lt;/title&gt;</code> tag etc.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n <div class=\"content\">\r\n	<table class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n		<tbody>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code></td>\r\n				<td>declaration defines this document to be HTML5</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td><code>&lt;html&gt;</code></td>\r\n				<td>root element of an HTML page</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td><code>&lt;head&gt;</code></td>\r\n				<td>contains meta information about the document</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td><code>&lt;title&gt;</code></td>\r\n				<td>specifies a title for the document</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td><code>&lt;body&gt;</code></td>\r\n				<td>contains the visible page content</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td><code>&lt;h1&gt;</code></td>\r\n				<td>defines a large heading</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td><code>&lt;p&gt;</code></td>\r\n				<td>defines a paragraph</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n		\r\n		</tbody>\r\n	</table>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p><strong># Example</strong></p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;title&gt;Page Title&lt;/title&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;h1&gt;This is heading 1&lt;/h1&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;h2&gt;This is heading 2&lt;/h2&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;h3&gt;This is heading 3&lt;/h3&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;h4&gt;This is heading 4&lt;/h4&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;h5&gt;This is heading 5&lt;/h5&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;h6&gt;This is heading 6&lt;/h6&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n    &lt;p&gt;My first paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n &lt;/body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;/html&gt;</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <a href=\"https://nexladder.com/codemirror/html/html-tags\" target=\"_blank\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-code\">Try it Yourself <i class=\"fa fa-arrow-circle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i></button></a>\r\n</div>',2,1,'HTML Tags - nexladder','learn html tags, html tutorial online, html tutorial beginners, professionals, introduction, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, lists, images, links, tables, frames, layouts, forms, style sheet and more.','Learn Html in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with tags, elements, tables, forms, anchor, image, heading, textarea, div etc',1,1529157396,'2018-06-16 13:56:36','2018-06-16 14:04:01'),(172,5,30,'HTML Attributes','html-attributes','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p>All HTML elements can have attributes and attributes provide additional information about an element. attributes are always specified in the <strong>start</strong> tag. attributes usually come in <code>name/value</code> pairs like: <code>name=\"value\"</code>.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <h2>The src Attribute</h2>\r\n <p>HTML images are defined with the <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tag.</p>\r\n <p>The filename of the image source is specified in the src attribute:</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <h3>Example</h3>\r\n <p>&lt;img src=\"\" alt=\"\" width=\"120\" height=\"40\" /&gt;</p>\r\n <p>The image size is specified in pixels. i.e width: 120px, height:40px</p>\r\n <p>img <code>alt</code> attribute is also useful if the image does not exist.</p>\r\n <p>img <code>alt</code> attribute specifies an alternative text to be used, when an image cannot be displayed.</p>\r\n</div>',3,1,'HTML Attributes - nexladder','learn html attributes, html tutorial online, html tutorial beginners, professionals, introduction, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, lists, images, links, tables, frames, layouts, forms, style sheet and more.','Learn Html in easy and simple steps starting from basic to advanced concepts with tags, elements, tables, forms, anchor, image, heading, textarea, div etc',1,1529157546,'2018-06-16 13:59:06','2018-06-16 13:59:06'),(173,5,30,'HTML Formatting','html-formatting','<div class=\"content\">\r\n  <p>HTML formatting tags are used for formatting a text style.There are many formatting tags in HTML. These tags are used to make text bold (<code>&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;</code>), italicized (<code>&lt;i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;</code>), or underlined (<code>&lt;u&gt;&lt;/u&gt;</code>).</p>\r\n  <p>\r\n	<table class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n		<tbody>\r\n			<tr>\r\n			  <th style=\"width: 20%;\">Tag</th>\r\n			  <th style=\"width: 40%;\">Example</th>\r\n			  <th style=\"width: 40%;\">Results</th>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n			  <td>&lt;b&gt;</td>\r\n			  <td>&lt;b&gt;Bold Text&lt;/b&gt; </td>\r\n			  <td>An example of&nbsp;<b>Bold Text</b></td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n			  <td>&lt;big&gt;</td>\r\n			  <td>&lt;big&gt;Big Text&lt;/big&gt;</td>\r\n			  <td>An example of&nbsp;<big>Big Text</big></td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n			  <td>&lt;center&gt;</td>\r\n			  <td>&lt;center&gt;Center Text&lt;/center&gt;</td>\r\n			  <td>An example of&nbsp;\r\n				<center>Center Text</center>\r\n			  </td>\r\n