argin-bottom</td>\r\n			<td>It is used to set bottom margin of an element.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n  </table>\r\n  \r\n  <h2>CSS Margin Properties</h2>\r\n  <table class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>Value</th>\r\n			<th>Description</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>auto</td>\r\n			<td>This is used to let the browser calculate a margin.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>length</td>\r\n			<td>It is used to specify a margin pt, px, cm, etc. its default value is 0px.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>%</td>\r\n			<td>It is used to define a margin in percent of the width of containing element.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>inherit</td>\r\n			<td>It is used to inherit margin from parent element.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n  </table>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p> <i class=\"fa fa-hand-o-down\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> See this example:</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"dec\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;html</span><span class=\"pln\"> </span><span class=\"atn\">lang</span><span class=\"pun\">=</span><span class=\"atv\">\"en\"</span><span class=\"tag\">&gt;</span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n</span><span class=\"tag\">&lt;head&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;title&gt;Example of CSS Margin&lt;/title&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;style&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">  \r\n	p.margin {</span><span class=\"tag\">  \r\n	    margin-top:35px;</span><span class=\"tag\">   \r\n	    margin-right:10px;</span><span class=\"tag\">   \r\n	    margin-bottom:75px;</span><span class=\"tag\">   \r\n	    margin-left:55px;</span><span class=\"tag\">    \r\n	}</span><span class=\"tag\">  	\r\n&lt;/style&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\"> \r\n&lt;/head&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">\r\n&lt;body&gt;</span><span class=\"tag\">  \r\n		&lt;h1&gt;Th