lass=\"pun\">(\'</span><span class=\"str\">vote</span><span class=\"pun\">\');</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">Route</span><span class=\"pun\">::</span><span class=\"kwd\">get</span><span class=\"pun\">(\'/</span><span class=\"str\">not-elligible</span><span class=\"pun\">\', \'</span><span class=\"pln\">UserController</span><span class=\"pun\">@</span><span class=\"str\">not_elligible</span><span class=\"pun\">\')-></span><span class=\"kwd\">name</span><span class=\"pun\">(\'</span><span class=\"str\">not_elligible</span><span class=\"pun\">\');</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>In above, we\'ve created the routes to understand the mechanism of middleware.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">public </span><span class=\"typ\">function </span><span class=\"pln\">handle</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">$request</span><span class=\"pun\">, </span><span class=\"kwd\">Closure </span><span class=\"pln\">$next</span><span class=\"pun\">)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n { </span><span class=\"pln\">\r\n        $age </span><span class=\"pun\">= </span><span class=\"pln\">$request</span><span class=\"pun\">-></span><span class=\"pln\">segment</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">2</span><span class=\"pun\">)</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n	if </span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">$age </span><span class=\"pun\">>= </span><span class=\"pln\">18</span><span class=\"pun\">)</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n	return </span><span class=\"str\">$next</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pln\">$request</span><span class=\"pun\">);</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n	 else</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n	return </span><span class=\"pln\">redirect</span><span class=\"pun\">()-></span><span class=\"pln\">route</span><span class=\"pun\">(\'</span><span class=\"str\">not_elligible</span><span class=\"pun\">\');</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n}</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>Copy the above <code>handle</code> method and replace it with <code>app/Http/Middleware/VoteMiddleware</code>\'s handle method.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n <p>To check middleware, visit your site using a URL similar to this one:</p>\r\n\r\n <p><i class=\"fa fa-link\">&nbsp;</i> http://127.0.0.1:8000/vote/18</p>\r\n\r\n <p><img src=\"https://nexladder.com/uploads/laravel_middleware.png\" class=\"img-responsive\" alt=\"Laravel Middleware\" /></p>\r\n\r\n <p>visit your site using a URL similar to this one:</p>\r\n\r\n <p><i class=\"fa fa-link\">&nbsp;</i> http://127.0.0.1:8000/vote/15 i.e second segment i.e 15 should be less than 18</p>\r\n\r\n <p>When we navigate to this link, it\'ll be redirected to <code>not_elligible</code> named route.</p>\r\n\r\n <p><img src=\"https://nexladder.com/uploads/laravel_middleware2.png\" class=\"img-responsive\" alt=\"Laravel Middleware\" /></p>\r\n</div>',6,1,'Laravel Middleware - nexladder','laravel middleware, middleware in laravel, laravel middleware example, example laravel middleware,  laravel middleware tutorial, beginners, professionals, mvc, basic concept, configuring, libraries, error handling, file uploading, sending email.','Learn Laravel Tutorial for beginners and professionals with examples on mvc, routing, models, Model, View, Controller, database configuration, crud, authentication etc.',1,1578322359,'2020-01-06 14:52:39','2020-01-23 16:33:40'),(224,13,34,'Laravel Controllers','laravel-controllers','<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>Controllers are the most important feature in MVC architecture. In MVC, <strong>\'C\'</strong> stands for controller.</p>\r\n<p>When we create the controller using artisan command, it\'ll be saved under <code>app/Http/Controllers</code> directory.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2># Basic Controllers</h2>\r\n<p>Controller can be created by executing the following artisan command -</p>\r\n<p><code>php artisan make:controller controller_name</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We\'ll create controller i.e <strong>UserController</strong> using artisan command.</p>\r\n<p><code>php artisan make:controller UserController</code></p>\r\n<p>it\'ll be created under <code>app/Http/Controllers/</code> directory.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>app/Http/Controllers/UserController.php</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"str\">&lt;?php </span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nnamespace </span><span class=\"str\">App</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Http</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Controllers</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nuse </span><span class=\"str\">Illuminate</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Http</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Request</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nuse </span><span class=\"str\">Illuminate</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Support</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Facades</span><span class=\"str\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Route</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n\r\nclass </span><span class=\"str\">UserController </span><span class=\"kwd\">extends </span><span class=\"str\">Controller </span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ {</span><span class=\"pun\"><span class=\'com\'>\r\nÂ  // Do Stuff</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ }</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<h2># Resource Controllers</h2>\r\n \r\n<p>Laravel resource controller makes it easier to create <strong>CRUD</strong> application. when we create an application we need to perform <strong>CRUD</strong> (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operation. Laravel makes this job easy for us and automatically provide all the methods in resource controller.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>To create the resource controller, we will first delete the UserController.php from the project, which we have created in the previous step.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Type below artisan command to generate resource controller.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>php artisan make:controller UserController --resource</code></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"str\">&lt;?php </span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nnamespace </span><span class=\"str\">App</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Http</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Controllers</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nuse </span><span class=\"str\">Illuminate</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Http</span><span class=\"pun\">\\</span><span class=\"str\">Request</span><span class=\"pun\">;</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\n\r\nclass </span><span class=\"str\">UserController </span><span class=\"kwd\">extends </span><span class=\"str\">Controller </span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ {</span><span class=\"pun\"><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nÂ  Â public </span><span class=\"pun\">function </span><span class=\"str\">index</span><span class=\"pun\">()</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â {</span><span class=\'com\'>\r\nÂ  Â  Â  // Display a listing of the resource.</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â }</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nÂ  Â public </span><span class=\"pun\">function </span><span class=\"str\">create</span><span class=\"pun\">()</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â {</span><span class=\'com\'>\r\nÂ  Â  Â  // Show the form for creating a new resource.</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â }</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nÂ  Â public </span><span class=\"pun\">function </span><span class=\"str\">store</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\'kwd\'>Request </span><span class=\'pln\'>$request</span><span class=\'pun\'>)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â {</span><span class=\'com\'>\r\nÂ  Â  Â  // Store a newly created resource in storage.</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â }</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nÂ  Â public </span><span class=\"pun\">function </span><span class=\"str\">show</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\'pln\'>$id</span><span class=\'pun\'>)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â {</span><span class=\'com\'>\r\nÂ  Â  Â  // Display the specified resource.</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â }</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nÂ  Â public </span><span class=\"pun\">function </span><span class=\"str\">edit</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\'pln\'>$id</span><span class=\'pun\'>)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â {</span><span class=\'com\'>\r\nÂ  Â  Â  // Show the form for editing the specified resource.</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â }</span><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nÂ  Â public </span><span class=\"pun\">function </span><span class=\"str\">update</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\'kwd\'>Request </span><span class=\'pln\'>$request</span><span class=\'pun\'>, </span><span class=\'pln\'>$id</span><span class=\'pun\'>)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â {</span><span class=\'com\'>\r\nÂ  Â  Â  // Update the specified resource in storage.</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â }</span><span class=\"kwd\"><span class=\"kwd\">\r\nÂ  Â public </span><span class=\"pun\">function </span><span class=\"str\">destroy</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\'pln\'>$id</span><span class=\'pun\'>)</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â {</span><span class=\'com\'>\r\nÂ  Â  Â  // Remove the specified resource from storage.</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\nÂ  Â }</span><span class=\"pun\">\r\n}</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>The above code contains the functions which are used to perform the various operations on the resources such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>create():</code> It is used to show the form for creating a new resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>store():</code> It is used to store a newly created resource in storage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>show():</code> It is used to display the specified resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>edit():</code> It is used to editing the specified resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>update():</code> It is used to update the specified resource in storage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>destroy():</code> It is used to remove the specified resource from storage.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>Add the following line of code in <code>app/Http/routes.php</code>.</p>\r\n<pre class=\"lang-php prettyprint prettyprinted\" style=\"\"><code><span class=\"kwd\">Route</span><span class=\"pun\">::</span><span class=\"str\">resource</span><span class=\"pun\">(</span><span class=\"pun\">\'</span><span class=\"pln\">user</span><span class=\"pun\">\', \'</span><span class=\"pun\">UserController</span><span class=\"pun\">\');</span></code>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content\">\r\n<p>We\'ll use artisan command to show a list of all the registered routes for the application.</p>\r\n<p><code>php artisan route:list</code></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://nexladder.com/uploads/laravel_route_list.png\" alt=\"Laravel Resource Routing\" class=\"img-responsive\" /></p>\r\n<div>',6,1,'Laravel Controllers - nexladder','laravel overview, tutorial, beginners, professionals, mvc, basic concept, configuring, libraries, error handling, file uploading, sending email.','Learn Laravel Tutorial for beginners and professionals with examples on mvc, routing, models, Model, View, Controller, database configuration, crud, authentication etc.',1,1578322412,'2020-01-06 14:53:32','2020-07-17 10:25:30'),(225,13,34,'Laravel Request','laravel-request','description to come',8,1,'Laravel Request - nexladder','laravel overview, tutorial, beginners, professionals, mvc, basic concept, configuring, libraries, error handling, file uploading, sending email.','Learn